# Lab 2 — Client → Coordinator → Server1 + Server2

Architecture (matches the Quack talk diagram):

  Client  →  Coordinator  →  Server1 (east shard, :9491)
                          →  Server2 (west shard, :9492)

Each box is DuckDB 1.5.3 + Quack in Docker.

## Start the cluster

cd lab2
docker compose up --build -d
docker compose ps

Wait until server1, server2, and coordinator are healthy.

## Run the client (from your Mac, DuckDB 1.5.3+)

/opt/homebrew/bin/duckdb -box < client.sql

Or interactively:

duckdb
CREATE SECRET (TYPE quack, SCOPE 'quack:localhost:9493', TOKEN 'coord_secret');
ATTACH 'quack:localhost:9493' AS coord (TYPE quack, DISABLE_SSL true);
FROM coord.all_orders ORDER BY id;

## Ports

| Service      | Host port | Token            |
|--------------|-----------|------------------|
| server1      | 9491      | server1_secret   |
| server2      | 9492      | server2_secret   |
| coordinator  | 9493      | coord_secret     |

## Direct shard access (skip coordinator)

CREATE SECRET (TYPE quack, SCOPE 'quack:localhost:9491', TOKEN 'server1_secret');
ATTACH 'quack:localhost:9491' AS s1 (TYPE quack, DISABLE_SSL true);
FROM s1.orders;

## Stop

docker compose down

## Logs

docker compose logs -f coordinator
docker compose logs -f server1
